11 An Act relating to the Oklahoma Children’s Code;
prohibiting certain actions by the Department of
12 Human Services in relation to adoptive and foster
parents; providing certain construction; providing
13 for codification; and providing an effective date.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-8-113 of Title 10A, unless
19 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. The Department of Human Services shall not:
21 1. Require any current or prospective adoptive or foster parent
22 to affirm, accept, or support any government policy regarding sexual
23 orientation or gender identity that conflicts with the parent’s
