1 sinc erely held religious or moral beliefs as a condition for
2 eligibility to adopt or foster;
3 2. Deny a current or prospective adoptive or foster parent any
4 authorization necessary to be eligible to adopt or foster based, in
5 whole or in part, upon the parent’s sincerely held religious or
6 moral beliefs, or intent to guide, instruct, or raise a child
7 consistent with those beliefs, regarding sexual orientation or
8 gender identity; or
9 3. Establish or enforce any standard, rule, or policy that
10 precludes consideration of a current or prospective adoptive or
11 foster parent for any particular placement based, in whole or in
12 part, upon the parent’s sincerely held religious or moral beliefs
13 regarding sexual orientation or gender identity.
14 B. Nothing in this section shall:
15 1. Preclude the Department from taking into account the
16 religious or moral beliefs of a particular adoptive or foster child,
17 or his or her family of origin including, but not limited to, the
18 child’s or family’s views regarding sexual orientation and gender
19 identity, considered in relation to the religious or moral beliefs
20 of a prospective adoptive or foster parent when determining which
21 placement is in the best interest of the child; or
22 2. Be construed to prohibit or relieve the Department of its
23 duty to make each placement consistent with the best interests of
24 the child as otherwise required by law.
